File: More than 60 churchgoers who attended the church gathering have since tested positive for the virus. JOHANNESBURG - The Duduza Clinic in Ekurhuleni has closed indefinitely after a nurse tested positive for COVID-19. She allegedly attended a prayer breakfast at the Divine Restoration Ministries in Bloemfontein in March. READ: KZN teacher dies of COVID-19 complications More than 60 churchgoers who attended the church gathering have since tested positive for the virus. ACDP's Reverend Kenneth Meshoe also attended and tested positive. READ: ACDP leader Kenneth Meshoe tests positive for COVID-19 Staff at the clinic who displayed symptoms have been tested and are self-isolating as they await their results. The nurse has been placed under quarantine. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.